FBIS3-36002 "drsov022_f_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-022 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Feb 1994 National Affairs Defense Ministry Updates Arms Reductions LD0102161094 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in English 0100 GMT 1 Feb 94 LD0102161094 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] According to the Defense Ministry's press service, 603 tanks, 630 armored cars, and 175 combat aircraft were scrapped in Ukraine by 17 November, 1993, in keeping with Ukraine's commitments under the treaty on conventional forces reductions in Europe. During 1993 over 50 international inspection teams visited Ukraine. They visited tank manufacturing and repair factories in Lvov, Nikolayev, Kiev, and Zhitomir, which are expected to shortly scrap a total of 100 tanks and 60 armored cars. The newest stage in Ukraine's conventional weaponry reductions provides for scrapping over 600 tanks and more than 300 armored cars.
